Topic of the workshop 	  =09
  The relationship between logic and category theory goes back to the
seventies, with the important connection between intuitionistic logic,
sheaves and topoi (1) but it extended into other directions, in
particular the proof as morphisms semantics (2), and we also include the
study of proof normalisation (3). Ideally, the workshop will consider
the three levels of foundations , according to the terminology of
Jean-Yves Girard, as well as their mutual relationships.
  These structures provide models of computation but also models of
meaning organisation des lexemes, phrases, sentences, discourses and
dialogues: we do not exclude the first application, but we shall
privilege the linguistic application which is quite new, although
Joachim Lambek suggested to do so more than twenty years ago. 	  	 =
